I have made egregious assumptions on purpose.  Those that know will
know enough to know and those that do not will only find this.  That I
say make bread, or toast, in that case, is because the simplicity of
it is in the creation.  All the magic one needs is in the simplicity
of such mystical action.  I could have said chop wood, carry water,
mystical action, magical power, but would that have made sense to
those who are looking for the dramatic displays of flourish.  Why
should you want to create a display of flowery when you could just
pick flowers.  Why would you want to light a candle with your mind,
when you can use a match.  Magic is about necessity, the ancient magic
is about knowledge and not power.  The most powerful magic is stepping
outside the comfort zone and doing something for someone else for no
reason.  The second most powerful magic is understanding, master these
and those mental powers, and amazing actions used to entertain the
royal peasants will be less difficult.  Or continue to believe that
the parlor is where you need to apply yourself, and miss the real
magic, breathing.

I am a hedge wizard, content to tend to my small flock and create
small magics for the children.  I need no flourish, because I know I
am and that is all that is really needed to make one magical.

Sleep well,
James
