Bread

To the initiate:
Go into the forest and gather the makings of the fire, as this must be
the first part of this lesson.

Now go to the well (or stream) and fetch a quantity of water.

You will bring the water to the place by the fire.  This will then be
where you will complete the creation.

Now go to the field and gather grains that are ripened, and if there
no grains that have ripened, go into the forest and gather the seed of
the hickory tree.

Bring these to the place of the fire and place them near the water.

You will need of two stones, one that is of a bowl, and one that is of
a hammer.  These will also be placed near the water, that is by the
place where the fire shall be.

You will now place the grains in the bowl, and add one handful of
water for every two handfuls of grain.  This will now rest, for the
time that it takes to build the fire.

You will now make the fire as you were instructed in previous lessons.

With the fire set you will place the bowl near to the fire and allow
it warm to the touch on the under of the wrist.

This will be wear the water must be kept, not higher or lower.

The rest will be given later...
